It’s a narrow line to walk, said Darry Sragow, a former Democratic campaign strategist who now publishes the nonpartisan California Target Book, which analyzes state political contests.
“If you’re a Democrat and looking to maximize Democratic turnout, attacks on the president and Republicans make sense,” he said.
“There’s no playbook on how either side of the aisle plays this.”In California congressional races, Republicans and Democrats alike are playing the virus card.
In one series of emails, the Democratic Congressional Campaign Committee charged that GOP candidates were backing Trump’s efforts to block uninsured coronavirus patients from signing up for health insurance.
That’s irresponsible, and we thought people should know this.”The Nunes campaign did not respond to a request for comment.